icers.  I am tired of modern-day civilization hiding behind the Constitution to perpetuate a Right that was established over two centuries ago.<br>
<br>
Think about those two women in Alabama during the road rage dispute.  They tage each other on the highway, pull over.  Woman 1 gets out of her vehicle angrily and approaches woman 2 in her vehicle.  Woman 2 imagines woman 1 is armed, pulls out a gun she has in her glove compartment, and shoots to death woman 1...who is unarmed.<br>
<br>
Now, several children are without mothers because one is dead and the other got sentenced to 25 to Life--and neither of them had criminal records.  Just one gun.<br>
<br>
Times are different now.  Take the guns away. <p><p><center><a><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~shay01/ajahn.gif" border="0"></center></a>

<p><center><a><img src="http://home.mindspring.com/~jtparris/_uimages/Valentina.1.gif" border="0"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/umorkenlar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Morkenlar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Councilman</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/24/02 3:54:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gun Control</span><hr size=1> Thats an example of someone having a weapon that caused harm.  You KNOW I can toss out examples of people having weapons preventing harm (at least to one party).  We could go back and forth forever on examples, as you well know.<br>
<br>
Bottom line, I don't think society has the right to restrict the rights of people to defend themselves in a reasonably expedient manner. <p></br>

<img src=http://home.attbi.com/~shay01/morksiggy.gif
>


</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/uxunathewizardess.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xuna the Wizardess</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/24/02 4:33:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gun Control</span><hr size=1> Same mother could have just as easily ran over the first mother.<br>
<br>
The key to Gun &quot;Control&quot; is education.<br>
<br>
I personally enjoy having several guns and my 2 children have a full working knowledge of these weapons.  But the key to this is that the &quot;mystery&quot; of the guns has been removed from thier minds so you will not see them playing with them.  <br>
<br>
I would support any law that required strict training and certification for anyone to own a firearm.  But thier are plenty of other ways for people to rashly kill one another.  <br>
<br>
Yes, its tired and cliche but Guns don't kill people.  People kill people.<br>
<br>
